  "text": "As shown in Fig. 4 and Table 1 , the genomic responses in patients correlated well with each other, whereas this response was mimicked poorly by the mouse models. The same relationship held for the directionality of the gene response. For example, in humans, correlations of 0.91 (trauma), 0.55 (ARDS), 0.54-0.79 (sepsis), and 0.50 (infection) were observed with percentage of the genes changing in the same direction of 97%, 84%, 86-92%, and 83%, respectively. For murine orthologs, there were correlations between 0 and 0.08, with 47-61% of genes changing in the same direction-random chance would predict 50%. In addition, published data with radiation injury [CITATION_1] showed similar results (SI Appendix, Fig. S9 ).",
